text: TNR may refer to: * TNR, the gene that encodes the protein Tenascin-R * Ivato International Airport,Antananarivo, Madagascar, IATA code * The New Republic, an American magazine of politics and the arts * Train Navette Rapide, an express train service in Morocco * Trap-neuter-return, a method for managing feral cats * T.N.Rajarathnam Pillai (1898-1956), Indian musician
title: TNR
